He said the cartel was trying to 
infiltrate all levels of society - and by the time La Familia morphed into 
the Knights Templar in 2010, it seemed to control the entire state, 
including politicians and police who failed to act.

More than seven years of military-style strikes failed to dislodge them, but the federal government was notably more successful after targeting the cartel's financial resources.

It took over the port of Lazaro Cardenas in November and named Mr Castillo in January as a commissioner with special powers to try to clean up Michoacan.

